body.description: Explore the sights, sounds, and textures of these flippable sensory fidget tubes! Kids build essential fine motor and sensory skills every time they fidget with the Sensory Trio Fidget Tubes from Learning Resources. Each sensory tube in this fidget toy pack engages a different sense through fun hands-on play—listen to falling beads as they tumble down the tube, watch the swirl of glitter to spot the hidden smiley faces, or feel the weight of falling sand as it cascades from one end to the other. The sensory fun doesn’t stop there—features including a twist-and-click and fun grabbable textures ensure that kids stay engaged while they build sensory and fine motor skills. Sized just right for little hands, the Sensory Trio Fidget Tubes are ready for fidget fun at home or on the go—keep these kids’ sensory toys in the play room for breaks, or stash them in the car for on-the-road fidgeting! From sensory bin essentials to fun ways to fidget, award-winning educational toys from Learning Resources engage kids’ hands, brains, and senses through screen-free, hands-on play. Designed to help lower stress, provide calm after challenges, and regulate emotions, these sensory toys give kids the tools they need to be the best versions of themselves. Made from durable, BPA-free plastic, our sensory toys are ready for years of learning fun at home or in the classroom. We're Learning Resources, and we've been helping parents and teachers build generations of amazing kids since 1984. From ABCs and 123s to fine motor and STEM skills, our educational toys offer kids the building blocks they need to succeed in school and develop a lifelong love of learning. Discover countless ways to learn through play with our award-winning products, including Toy of the Year winners Tumble Trax, Botley the Coding Robot, and Coding Critters. Learn more about how we turn a childhood love of play into a lifelong love of learning with a visit to our brand store today.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just What We Needed
reviews.reviewText: I have three boys ages 11, 5, and 1. We own a lot of sensory toys and fidgets. The baby often wants to use them as well. The other day he got ahold of one of the more traditional water toys and smacked it hard enough it broke open everywhere. You’d think the stuff in them is benign, apparently it’s not. I bathed him right away but he has a blistering rash, his whole leg has swelled, and he is miserable. I knew we needed something that was going to be safe for him to play with that was similar to the “big kid” toys. These are perfect! We’ve only had them a few hours but my very rough five year old has already put them through their paces. I feel confident allowing the baby to play with these.These are a good size. Not too tall/long so no risk of him accidentally smacking himself as he shakes them. They have a chubby rounded shape that’s easy to grip. Two make interesting noises. The plastic seems tough and durable. I’d happily recommend these to any home with toddlers or less than gentle children. Might be a good option in occupational settings too since so many kids and adults could enjoy these. In terms of occupational settings we would warn that the sand does make a noise that all of us can hear but it’s not bothering anyone. I could see the rain stick one being problematic to some sensitive individuals though. It’s not quiet by our standards (myself and the 5yo are sound sensitive). It’s not bothering my 11yo though.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good sensory toys!
reviews.reviewText: Toys arrived safely in a plastic blister pack, so no doubt at all that they were new.The rain stick looks cute and sounds pretty nice, and also has this feature where you can turn the caps at both ends and it clicks? Kind of random, but I guess it’s added value.The sand one is very calming, although something may be slightly wrong in one direction- turned one way the sand falls slowly, but turned the other way it all just dumps into one layer and then trickles out of that layer. Not sure if it’s supposed to be like that.The glitter one has cute smiley face shaped glitters in it. I do wish something was added to the water to make the glitter fall slower. This seems like it’s in plain water, so the glitter basically just Sinks instead of floating around much when disturbed.However, these are really small complaints- overall these are good! And I think it was a good deal for the three of them when I bought them, although I know Amazon prices change a lot.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for little hands
reviews.reviewText: These are great sensory toys for little hands. Easy to grasp and turn over for full effect.

My autistic son this set as one of his birthday presents and he really likes them! His favourite is the one with the purple sand inside. The sand moving through the tube sounds very relaxing, which he loves. He isn't a fan of the one with the marbles inside because its a bit loud, but he might enjoy it later on as he gets more familiar with these toys. Fidget toys can be hit or miss, but these are decent quality and great for kids who like visual and auditory input that is calming.
